    <h2>The Challenge</h2>
    <p>A leading North American energy company operating over 40 production and processing facilities faced a critical challenge: its integrity management practices varied significantly from site to site. Some facilities used commercial software, others relied on spreadsheets, and a few still maintained paper-based inspection records. This inconsistency made it impossible for corporate leadership to assess enterprise-wide integrity risk or benchmark performance across sites.</p>
    <p>The lack of standardization also created inefficiency. Each facility had developed its own workflows, reporting formats, and data structures. Engineers transferring between sites required extensive retraining, and corporate audits consumed disproportionate resources because each facility presented information differently.</p>

    <h2>The Solution</h2>
    <p>The company selected <strong>Visions Enterprise</strong> as its enterprise-wide AIM platform, deploying it across all operating facilities over a 24-month phased implementation. The deployment included standardized equipment hierarchies, consistent damage mechanism libraries, unified inspection workflows, and enterprise-level reporting dashboards.</p>
    <p>A dedicated implementation team worked with each facility to migrate legacy data, configure site-specific parameters within the standardized framework, and train local personnel. Corporate integrity standards were embedded in the platform configuration, ensuring consistent application regardless of local practices.</p>

    <h2>The Results</h2>
    <p>The enterprise deployment delivered transformative results:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Enterprise-wide risk visibility</strong> for the first time, enabling corporate leadership to allocate capital based on comparative risk data across all 40+ facilities.</li>
      <li><strong>30% reduction in total inspection costs</strong> through standardized RBI implementation that eliminated site-by-site variation in inspection philosophy.</li>
      <li><strong>Engineer mobility improved dramatically</strong>, with personnel able to transfer between facilities without retraining on different systems or workflows.</li>
      <li><strong>Audit preparation time reduced by 60%</strong> through standardized, on-demand reporting that provided consistent documentation across all sites.</li>
    </ul>
    <blockquote>For the first time, we can see our entire integrity risk profile on a single screen. That visibility has fundamentally changed how we prioritize investment across our portfolio.</blockquote>

    <h2>Ongoing Value</h2>
    <p>With the platform fully deployed, the company continues to derive increasing value through advanced analytics that identify trends across the enterprise. Cross-facility corrosion rate benchmarking has uncovered several instances where a facility's experience could inform better practices at other sites, creating a continuous improvement loop that would have been impossible without a unified data platform.</p>
